SAP 4.7 to S/4HANA Product Migration Tool - Observations and Recommendations 

Current State 

Current app loads mapping Excel, value mapping Excel, SAP 4.7 CSV extracts, builds a dataframe, applies mappings and generates XML. 

Major Issue 

Current XML output is generic Products XML. SAP Migration Cockpit template is SpreadsheetML Excel 2003 XML and must be preserved. 

SAP Template Observations 

Skip worksheets Introduction and Field List. Skip rows with styles INTRO and INTRO_UT. 

Missing Functionality 

Join logic between MARA, MAKT, MARC, MBEW, MLAN, MARM and other SAP source tables is required. 

Business Rules 

WAERS derived from BWKEY. MLAST=3. CURTP=10. ENTITLED derived from LGNUM. 

Value Mapping 

Use map(...).fillna(original) and collect unmapped values. 

Error Handling 

Maintain error collector, error report dialog, and logging. 

XML Strategy 

Open SAP XML template, preserve workbook structure, clone data rows, populate worksheets, save SpreadsheetML output. 

Recommended Architecture 

Load CSVs -> Mapping -> Joins -> Value Mapping -> Business Rules -> Final DataFrame -> Populate SAP SpreadsheetML -> Generate output XML. 

Assessment 

UI, logging, mappings and progress bar are good. XML generation layer must be redesigned to support SAP SpreadsheetML. 
